# Project Structure Guide

This project is organized as follows:

- The **client/** directory contains the frontend React application (TypeScript, Vite, TanStack Query, Lucide icons, Tailwind CSS).
  - Main entry: [client/src/main.tsx](mdc:client/src/main.tsx)
  - Pages: [client/src/pages/](mdc:client/src/pages/)
  - Components: [client/src/components/](mdc:client/src/components/)
  - Hooks: [client/src/hooks/](mdc:client/src/hooks/)
  - Theme and styles: [client/src/theme.css](mdc:client/src/theme.css), [client/src/index.css](mdc:client/src/index.css)
- The **server/** directory contains backend logic (API, routes, storage, Vite config).
  - Main entry: [server/index.ts](mdc:server/index.ts)
  - Routing: [server/routes.ts](mdc:server/routes.ts)
- The **shared/** directory contains shared TypeScript types and schema definitions.
  - [shared/schema.ts](mdc:shared/schema.ts)
- Project configuration and tooling files are in the root (e.g., [package.json](mdc:package.json), [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json), [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts)).

Use this structure to quickly locate files and understand the separation of concerns between frontend, backend, and shared code.
